From Jayne Kulikauskas Subject RE Does God love you Dave Mielke writes However God's love is The Bible says The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the LORD but he loveth him that followeth after Proverbs For the LORD knoweth the way of the righteous but the way of the ungodly shall Psalm I am extremely uncomfortable with this way of phrasing God's love is unconditional unqualified We are capable of rejecting God's love but He never fails to love These verses do not show that God's love is qualified but rather that He is opposed to I am uncomfortable with the tract in general because there seems to be an innappropriate emphasis on God deserves our love and worship because of who He I do not like the idea of frightening people into accepting I see evangelism as combining a way of living that shows God's love with putting into words and explaining that Preaching the Gospel without living the Gospel is no better than being a noisy gong or a clanging Here's a question How many of you are Christians because you are afraid of going to Hell How many are responding to God's love Jayne Kulikauskas